# Architecture and Design-System Guardrails

## Module Placement (Hard)
- New domain code must live under `src/modules/<domain>`.
- Cross-domain reusable UI must live under `src/shared`.
- Do not add new components under legacy `src/components/*`.
- For new components in module code, do not import from legacy `@/components/*`.

## Barrel Exports (Hard)
- Do not create new barrel files (`index.ts` / `index.tsx`) for exports.
- Prefer direct file imports with explicit local extensions when required by lint/CI.
- When touching a folder that has a barrel, do not add new barrel dependencies; prefer direct imports.

## Design-System Usage
- Use existing design-system tokens/patterns first.
- Raw gradients are allowed when intentional.
- For `boxShadow`, avoid one-off literals (`rgba`, hex, custom px shadow strings) in feature UI.
- Prefer theme shadow tokens or established reusable shadow constants/patterns.
- For surfaces/cards/backgrounds and paired states, prefer semantic tokens or `useColorModeValue(...)` patterns already used in the codebase.

## Reusability Decision Rule
- If a visual/state pattern is used in more than one place, update the design system/shared layer first.
- Only keep local one-off styles when they are intentionally unique and unlikely to be reused.

## i18n Preference
- Prefer punctuation outside `t()` where practical.
- This punctuation rule is advisory (non-blocking) unless explicitly requested for strict cleanup.

## GraphQL Hook Rule
- Use generated hooks from `@/types`.
- Do not use Apollo base hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useLazyQuery`) in feature code.

## Icon Package Rule
- Prefer `react-icons/pi` for new icon additions.
- Do not churn existing non-`pi` icon imports unless the file is already being updated for functional reasons.

## Existing Behavior
- Preserve current behavior unless the task explicitly requires behavior changes.
- If docs and implementation differ, either align docs to accepted behavior or document a deliberate migration plan before changing runtime behavior.
